---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Support - Ember by PulseLab" description="Get help with Ember. FAQs, troubleshooting, and contact information.">
  <section class="pt-32 pb-8 px-8 bg-[var(--ember-bg)]">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <a href="/ember" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[var(--ember-primary)] mb-6 hover:underline">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M19 12H5M12 19l-7-7 7-7"/>
        </svg>
        Back to Ember
      </a>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--ember-text)] mb-2">Support</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-[var(--ember-primary)]">Ember by PulseLab</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-8 px-8">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="contact-card ember-contact">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-dark)] mb-3">Need Help?</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--text-medium)] mb-5">We're here to help you get the most out of Ember. Send us an email and we'll get back to you as soon as possible.</p>
        <a href="mailto:hello@pulselab.cc?subject=Ember%20Support" class="btn btn-primary ember-btn">Email Support</a>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-dark)] mt-12 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Is my health data private?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Yes, completely. All your data is stored locally on your device and never transmitted to our servers. We literally cannot see your health information. Read our <a href="/ember/privacy" class="ember-link">Privacy Policy</a> for more details.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Do I need to create an account?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">No. Ember works entirely without an account. This is part of our privacy-first design - no accounts means no personal information stored on servers.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">How do I back up my data?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Your Ember data is included in your iPhone backup (iCloud or local). When you restore your phone from a backup, your Ember data will be restored as well. You can also export PDF reports to save your symptom history.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Can I use Ember on multiple devices?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Since Ember stores data locally and doesn't use cloud sync (for privacy), each device will have its own separate data. We recommend using Ember on your primary iPhone.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">How does Apple Health integration work?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">When you enable Apple Health integration, Ember can read your sleep, heart rate, and HRV data to help identify correlations with your symptoms. This data is processed entirely on your device and never sent anywhere.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">What symptoms can I track?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Ember supports 20+ perimenopause and menopause symptoms including hot flashes, night sweats, sleep disruptions, mood changes, brain fog, anxiety, joint pain, headaches, and more. You can also add custom notes to any entry.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">How do I share reports with my doctor?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Go to the Reports tab, select a date range, and generate a PDF. You can then share it via email, AirDrop, print it, or save it to Files. The report is created on your device and you control how it's shared.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3 class="faq-question">How much does Ember cost?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Ember is a one-time purchase of $9.99. There are no subscriptions, no in-app purchases, and no ads. Pay once, use forever.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-dark)] mt-12 mb-6">Getting the Most from Ember</h2>

      <div class="tips-list">
        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon ember-icon">
            <span>üìù</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h3>Track Consistently</h3>
            <p>Try to log symptoms at the same times each day. Consistent tracking helps Ember identify patterns more accurately.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon ember-icon">
            <span>‚åö</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h3>Enable Apple Health</h3>
            <p>If you have an Apple Watch, enabling Health integration provides richer insights about how your sleep and activity relate to symptoms.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon ember-icon">
            <span>üìã</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h3>Prepare for Doctor Visits</h3>
            <p>Generate a report before your healthcare appointments. Having objective data helps facilitate better conversations about your care.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon ember-icon">
            <span>üîê</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h3>Enable Biometric Lock</h3>
            <p>For extra privacy, enable Face ID or Touch ID in Settings to protect your health data from others who might use your phone.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .contact-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .ember-btn {
    background: var(--gradient-ember) !important;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(212, 88, 58, 0.35);
  }

  .ember-btn:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(212, 88, 58, 0.45);
  }

  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .faq-question {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .faq-answer {
    color: var(--text-medium);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .ember-link {
    color: var(--ember-primary);
  }

  .tips-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .tip-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .tip-icon {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    background: var(--gradient);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ember-icon {
    background: var(--gradient-ember);
  }

  .tip-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .tip-content p {
    color: var(--text-medium);
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .tip-card {
      flex-direction: column;
      text-align: center;
      align-items: center;
    }
  }
</style>
